<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-20T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-20T14:00:00-05:00" n="1284" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1284">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/310</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Collector <persName type="from">Cobb</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-20T12:00:00-07:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 20, 1917, noon</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Informed confidentially by party whose agent at Chihuahua was approached
                            that Chihuahua Government authorities are calling for forced loan of
                            twenty-five thousand dollars. This in spite of the fact that they have
                            money on deposit in El Paso. My June 19, noon.<note n="2" xml:id="d1284fn2">Not printed.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cobb</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>